        "committer": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-08-29 01:48:21.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 ldlm: prolong timeout of waiting lock",
        "message": "LU-0000 ldlm: prolong timeout of waiting lock\n\nthis patch covered a couple of workarounds for testing only:\n\n- when server sends back lock reply for ldlm_lock_enqueue, and if\n  the lock already has queued blocking AST, we should make sure\n  timeout of lock expire timer is long enough at least for client\n  to resend lock enqueue, otherwise if reply is lost or congested\n  on router for long enough, then client will be evicted.\n\n  This workaround can't help for the multiple messages lost case.\n\n- there is no guarantee that req::rq_timeout is lower than\n  ldlm_bl_timeout, which means it is possible that lock wait timer\n  is expired but RPC is not timedout yet.\n  This patch will make sure ldlm_add_waiting_lock can wait longer\n  than both ldlm_bl_timeout and req::rq_timeout\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang.zhen@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ic440b2a2a47c9cd8a1c2fed8da94659157a72969\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
